                <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.88);">The revenue schedule usually lands with whoever signed the contracts, so a founder or a sales lead spends the last night of the month piecing terms together in a spreadsheet. That is qualified accounting work being done by people whose day job is selling. Giving the ledger to an accountant returns those evenings to the product.</p>
